expected prefixes. Host connectivity is successful end-to-end.\n\nRoot-cause analysis\n- Because there are no functional failures (no BGP sessions DOWN, no missing routes, no packet loss), there is nothing to trace to a root cause of an outage. The current state indicates normal convergence of EBGP in this lab topology.\n\nAdditional notes / recommendations for next steps (if you want them)\n- I did not run detailed per-interface diagnostics (ethtool/tc counters) or continuous long-duration traffic tests. If you suspect intermittent issues, collecting interface error counters and sustained iperf tests could be useful.\n- If you want me to verify specific BGP neighbor states or inspect logs for historical flaps, I can pull BGP neighbor statuses and FRR logs.\n\nConclusion\n- Current assessment: network is healthy and functioning as intended. BGP is converged and hosts can reach one another with no packet loss in the sampled tests. No configuration or runtime anomalies that impact reachability were found.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8766, "output_tokens": 3445, "total_tokens": 12211, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 3840}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2048}}}
